<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1922-11-09T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1922-11-09T18:00:00-05:00" n="874" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d874">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">837.51/880: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Representative on Special Mission in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crowder</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-11-09T18:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">November 9,
                                        1922—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>80. Your 75, November 8, 5 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Lee, Higginson and Company sending representative Cuba Friday or Saturday
                            if assured Cuban Government wishes competitive bidding. Other bankers
                            also interested. Please telegraph as early as possible manner in which
                            loan will be negotiated.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>